transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Olivia speaking. Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 2: Juan Reyes.

Speaker 1: Hi Juan, how are you?

Speaker 2: I'm good, thanks.

Speaker 1: Great, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: I would like to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can help you with this. Okay Juan, what is your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 03-24-81.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I see you here. Okay, so this refill from today you don't want it nor need it, is that correct?

Speaker 2: Yes, I don't need it. I noticed that they already withdrew the money, I'm not sure if they already did.

Speaker 1: That's why I was calling you because I don't need them. I didn't know it was a subscription, so that's why.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Okay, I just canceled and refunded the order for you so you will not receive it, but you should see that refund soon. And if you don't want to receive regular refills with your prescription, you certainly don't have to.

Speaker 2: You always have the option to place your prescription on hold for up to six months at a time just because six months is when the prescription would expire if we didn't refill it.

Speaker 1: And the way that would work is whenever you are ready to order, if it is before then, you can. You just have to give us a call to place the order yourself.

Speaker 2: Okay, sounds good. I'll have that online.

Speaker 1: Okay, great. So yeah, if you need anything before August 12th, just give us a call. We're always here Monday through Friday and you should see that refund soon.

Speaker 2: All right, thank you very much. Appreciate it for your help.

Speaker 1: Thanks, Juan. Have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye.
